1
00:00:17,440 --> 00:00:21,340
I'm more scared about losing you
than losing an opportunity...

2
00:00:22,210 --> 00:00:24,700
in this industry because of a scandal.

3
00:00:25,580 --> 00:00:26,750
So...

4
00:00:29,150 --> 00:00:30,660
let's start over again.

5
00:00:36,450 --> 00:00:38,510
Are you still not going to hold onto me?

6
00:00:42,990 --> 00:00:44,240
If you let go now,

7
00:00:46,430 --> 00:00:49,360
we'll never get to see each other again.

8
00:01:12,220 --> 00:01:13,330
Ms. Oh Jin Sim.

9
00:01:23,300 --> 00:01:24,310
I love you.

10
00:01:58,340 --> 00:02:00,150
(Episode 15)

11
00:02:03,810 --> 00:02:05,050
We're here already.

12
00:02:06,180 --> 00:02:07,620
Why is my place so nearby?

13
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:15,570
I don't want to go home today.

14
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:19,720
I want to be with you.

15
00:02:21,590 --> 00:02:23,980
To be honest, I feel the same way.

16
00:02:27,060 --> 00:02:28,950
Can I go home after I see you fall asleep?

17
00:02:45,220 --> 00:02:47,060
It takes quite a while
for me to fall asleep.

18
00:02:47,790 --> 00:02:48,960
That's better.

19
00:02:49,090 --> 00:02:51,110
That means I'll get to
see you for a long time.

20
00:02:52,190 --> 00:02:55,720
My insomnia never really bothered me.

21
00:02:56,630 --> 00:03:00,130
But after we broke up,
my insomnia started...

22
00:03:01,170 --> 00:03:02,310
giving me a hard time.

23
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:08,200
I had to stay up all night
thinking about you.

24
00:03:12,740 --> 00:03:15,330
When was the hardest for you?

25
00:03:16,980 --> 00:03:20,050
Never mind. You were probably fine
because you were so busy.

26
00:03:21,820 --> 00:03:24,010
Who says I didn't have a hard time?

27
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:27,380
I had a hard time every night
and every morning.

28
00:03:28,290 --> 00:03:30,310
I had a hard time working
and going to trials.

29
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:33,270
Every minute of the day
was difficult for me.

30
00:03:34,570 --> 00:03:35,440
Really?

31
00:03:35,660 --> 00:03:37,530
Did you really have that
much of a hard time?

32
00:03:37,540 --> 00:03:40,800
Are you that happy to hear
that I had a hard time?

33
00:03:41,410 --> 00:03:45,070
Of course. That shows how
much you really liked me.

34
00:03:46,310 --> 00:03:48,770
Oddly enough, I feel very relieved now.

35
00:03:59,060 --> 00:04:02,320
Let's never break up again.

36
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:04,810
Let's promise each other...

37
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:07,980
that we'll never let go
of each other's hands.

38
00:04:10,630 --> 00:04:13,020
Okay, I promise.

39
00:04:15,910 --> 00:04:17,320
I won't ever let go.

40
00:04:18,310 --> 00:04:21,610
And I'll protect you.

41
00:04:25,150 --> 00:04:28,380
The reason I left you was...

42
00:04:29,450 --> 00:04:32,080
because I didn't want to bother you...

43
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:34,000
since it was such an important
time in your career.

44
00:04:35,030 --> 00:04:37,010
And I still feel the same way.

45
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:40,380
So for the sake of protecting you,

46
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:44,030
we should do a better job in
keeping our relationship a secret.

47
00:04:44,340 --> 00:04:47,460
We should do a better job in
keeping our relationship a secret?

48
00:04:47,470 --> 00:04:50,710
Yes, we can't have anyone take
photos of us like last time.

49
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:53,260
So we should refrain from meeting outside.

50
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:55,900
We should meet up in confined areas...

51
00:04:56,350 --> 00:04:59,170
such as your place or mine from now on.

52
00:05:03,220 --> 00:05:06,150
Confined areas?

53
00:05:07,220 --> 00:05:08,240
Yes.

54
00:05:09,460 --> 00:05:12,320
A secret and quiet place
where there's no one else...

55
00:05:12,700 --> 00:05:13,710
but the two of us.

56
00:05:21,510 --> 00:05:22,520
Is it okay...

57
00:05:23,670 --> 00:05:25,220
if I spend the night here?

58
00:05:41,030 --> 00:05:42,800
I won't ever cross this line.

59
00:05:43,330 --> 00:05:45,920
I promised you earlier
that I'll protect you.

60
00:05:47,100 --> 00:05:48,380
Oh, okay.

61
00:06:26,070 --> 00:06:28,690
Thank you so much for protecting me.

62
00:06:47,220 --> 00:06:49,910
- Good morning, Mr. Kwon.
- Good morning.

63
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:55,130
It must've been uncomfortable
for you to sleep in that.

64
00:06:55,230 --> 00:06:56,240
It's okay.

65
00:06:56,830 --> 00:06:58,300
What's your schedule for today?

66
00:06:58,300 --> 00:06:59,950
I'm not that busy today.

67
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:02,790
My shoot starts at 1pm,

68
00:07:02,970 --> 00:07:04,550
and it'll probably end at about 7pm.

69
00:07:05,340 --> 00:07:07,430
Then we can have dinner together.

70
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:10,430
- I'll call as soon as I'm done.
- Okay.

71
00:07:13,080 --> 00:07:14,160
Who's here so early in the morning?

72
00:07:18,090 --> 00:07:19,990
It's my manager. What are we going to do?

73
00:07:19,990 --> 00:07:21,800
- Yun Seo.
- He'll be suspicious of us...

74
00:07:21,930 --> 00:07:23,240
if he sees us together at this hour.

75
00:07:24,230 --> 00:07:26,950
- Let's pretend like we're not here.
- Yun Seo.

76
00:07:27,430 --> 00:07:29,820
No, we can't do that.
He knows the passcode.

77
00:07:29,830 --> 00:07:32,060
If I don't answer,
he'll probably just come in.

78
00:07:32,070 --> 00:07:33,810
- What should I do?
- Why does he know your passcode?

79
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,060
I get that he's your manager,
but he should...

80
00:07:35,070 --> 00:07:36,450
- respect your privacy.
- I'm going in.

81
00:07:40,380 --> 00:07:41,420
What...

82
00:07:43,950 --> 00:07:45,530
You should hide here for now.

83
00:07:45,620 --> 00:07:46,960
What? Ms. Oh.

84
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:49,760
My gosh.

85
00:07:51,990 --> 00:07:54,110
Hey, you're up.

86
00:07:54,730 --> 00:07:57,150
I thought you were sleeping
because you didn't open the door.

87
00:07:57,390 --> 00:07:59,270
Oh, well...

88
00:07:59,860 --> 00:08:02,120
I was using the blender.

89
00:08:02,570 --> 00:08:03,910
That's why I didn't hear you ring the bell.

90
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,720
What brings you here so
early in the morning?

91
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:10,760
Doesn't the shoot start at 1pm?

92
00:08:10,770 --> 00:08:12,880
I got a call saying they changed the time.

93
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:15,200
Your shoot starts at 11am,
so we need to get going.

94
00:08:16,210 --> 00:08:17,290
I see. Okay.

95
00:08:17,620 --> 00:08:20,200
I'll get ready really quickly
and meet you downstairs.

96
00:08:20,250 --> 00:08:22,210
You can wait for me in the car.

97
00:08:22,220 --> 00:08:23,850
- I'll be right there.
- Okay, don't take too long.

98
00:08:23,850 --> 00:08:24,900
Okay.

99
00:08:28,460 --> 00:08:31,050
Oh, I almost forgot.
Yun Seo, let me use your bathroom.

100
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:34,780
Hyuk Joon!

101
00:08:36,270 --> 00:08:38,150
- What?
- I'm sorry.

102
00:08:39,100 --> 00:08:40,350
Can you not go to the bathroom?

103
00:08:40,570 --> 00:08:41,820
- Why not?
- What?

104
00:08:42,410 --> 00:08:45,330
- Well, the thing is...
- Yun Seo.

105
00:08:45,540 --> 00:08:49,140
I'm really sorry,
but my bladder is about to burst.

106
00:08:49,150 --> 00:08:50,950
- Please let me in.
- No, wait.

107
00:08:50,950 --> 00:08:52,350
- No, I really need to go.
- Hyuk Joon!

108
00:08:52,350 --> 00:08:53,730
I really need to go.

109
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:55,800
My gosh.

110
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:06,150
Yun Seo, how long are you
going to stand there?

111
00:09:06,730 --> 00:09:09,630
- Oh, right. I'm... I'm sorry.
- Yes, you should be.

112
00:09:09,900 --> 00:09:11,680
You should feel sorry for my bladder.
Please leave.

113
00:09:12,170 --> 00:09:13,250
- Go.
- Okay.

114
00:09:13,340 --> 00:09:14,380
Hurry.

115
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:54,560
Got you!

116
00:09:56,280 --> 00:09:57,290
Mr. Kwon?

117
00:09:59,380 --> 00:10:02,420
Yes, this is he. An investigation
by the prosecution?

118
00:10:06,560 --> 00:10:07,570
Gosh.

119
00:10:08,590 --> 00:10:09,640
You see...

120
00:10:10,490 --> 00:10:12,440
My gosh. It wasn't me!

121
00:10:12,860 --> 00:10:14,890
Goodness...

122
00:10:15,500 --> 00:10:16,780
My gosh,

123
00:10:17,030 --> 00:10:18,080
Mr. Kwon.

124
00:10:22,710 --> 00:10:25,430
It's all right.
I was going to shower anyway.

125
00:10:26,740 --> 00:10:28,210
(Singil 3-dong Morning Soccer Club)

126
00:10:28,210 --> 00:10:29,590
Oh, dear.

127
00:10:33,180 --> 00:10:36,780
I'm glad that he had something
like this in his car.

128
00:10:39,220 --> 00:10:41,550
I'll wash this and get it back to you.

129
00:10:41,560 --> 00:10:42,840
So what's going on?

130
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:46,930
Why are you here this morning?

131
00:10:47,530 --> 00:10:48,940
No way. Hold on.

132
00:10:49,930 --> 00:10:51,250
Did you sleep here?

133
00:10:52,470 --> 00:10:53,470
- No!
- Yes.

134
00:10:53,470 --> 00:10:55,460
No and yes. Yes and no!

135
00:10:55,740 --> 00:10:57,680
That says it all. Mr. Kwon,

136
00:10:57,740 --> 00:11:00,430
it's true that I approve of you two dating,

137
00:11:00,540 --> 00:11:02,770
but this is completely inappropriate.

138
00:11:02,780 --> 00:11:03,820
Hyuk Joon!

139
00:11:04,820 --> 00:11:06,460
Mr. Kwon, you should get going.

140
00:11:06,950 --> 00:11:09,140
You barely have time to
go home and get changed.

141
00:11:09,290 --> 00:11:10,360
Come on.

142
00:11:14,060 --> 00:11:16,750
Mr. Kwon, I'm not finished, you know.

143
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:21,150
Does she not know how messed up this is?

144
00:11:29,170 --> 00:11:30,180
Here.

145
00:11:31,740 --> 00:11:33,960
- Bye.
- I'll get going then.

146
00:11:49,830 --> 00:11:51,960
Hyuk Joon, how could you say that to him...

147
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:54,420
when he got hosed down because of you?

148
00:11:54,430 --> 00:11:55,480
Yun Seo.

149
00:11:56,170 --> 00:11:59,930
He may have gotten hosed down,
but I was struck by a lightning.

150
00:12:00,270 --> 00:12:04,310
How can you bring him home
when you've barely been dating?

151
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:07,670
What should I do then?
Be with him on the streets...

152
00:12:07,680 --> 00:12:08,750
and get photographed?

153
00:12:08,750 --> 00:12:11,910
If you at least get photographed outside,

154
00:12:11,920 --> 00:12:13,490
I can make up a cover story.

155
00:12:13,550 --> 00:12:15,820
If he's photographed on
his way out of here,

156
00:12:15,820 --> 00:12:17,320
that's a done deal.

157
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:21,010
We're aware of that,
so we take necessary precautions.

158
00:12:21,020 --> 00:12:24,120
You approved our relationship,
so just let us be.

159
00:12:24,230 --> 00:12:25,270
Pretend you didn't see anything.

160
00:12:33,270 --> 00:12:34,720
That's what I want to do,

161
00:12:35,470 --> 00:12:37,180
but I'm worried that you'd get caught.

162
00:12:37,270 --> 00:12:39,190
I approved, but my brain
still doesn't allow it.

163
00:12:39,740 --> 00:12:40,990
It's driving me insane too.

164
00:12:45,420 --> 00:12:46,660
What are you looking at?

165
00:12:57,230 --> 00:13:00,660
What's this?
I was wondering where you were.

166
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:02,410
Were you out playing soccer?

167
00:13:04,170 --> 00:13:07,170
Hold on. Singil 3-dong Morning Soccer Club?

168
00:13:08,670 --> 00:13:09,950
Why go that far to play soccer?

169
00:13:11,910 --> 00:13:13,020
They must be good.

170
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:14,990
Let me join you next time.

171
00:13:15,310 --> 00:13:17,610
You'll never be able to join me there.

172
00:13:17,610 --> 00:13:20,070
What? Why not?

173
00:13:20,780 --> 00:13:22,560
Are they picky with the
members they accept?

174
00:13:22,890 --> 00:13:24,160
I'm quite good, you know.

175
00:13:24,990 --> 00:13:27,580
Just know that it's not a place for you.

176
00:13:30,590 --> 00:13:31,610
Seriously?

177
00:13:32,100 --> 00:13:34,790
Just how good is he at
soccer to shut me out?

178
00:13:50,580 --> 00:13:52,700
Who knew that I'd end up doing this?

179
00:14:05,730 --> 00:14:07,170
You finish around 7pm,

180
00:14:07,230 --> 00:14:08,640
but I'm texting in advance
because I miss you.

181
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:10,380
Are you done filming?

182
00:14:12,370 --> 00:14:15,470
I think it'll be over soon.
How about some dinner?

183
00:14:16,610 --> 00:14:17,620
That'd be great.

184
00:14:18,180 --> 00:14:20,260
Then I'll see you at my place.

185
00:14:21,950 --> 00:14:24,200
Will I be hosed down again?

186
00:14:25,580 --> 00:14:28,140
Of course not. I'm changing
my lock combination...

187
00:14:28,190 --> 00:14:29,660
as soon as I get home today.

188
00:14:31,590 --> 00:14:34,760
Then I'll bring you sushi, your favorite.

189
00:14:48,670 --> 00:14:50,370
Yes, I'm just about to...

190
00:14:50,370 --> 00:14:53,970
I'm sorry, but I'll have to stay
for some additional scenes.

191
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:56,600
I'm afraid I'll have to take a rain check.

192
00:14:58,050 --> 00:15:00,370
I see. Well, it can't be helped.

193
00:15:00,920 --> 00:15:03,880
Please don't tell me you
already bought the sushi.

194
00:15:05,060 --> 00:15:06,830
No, not yet.

195
00:15:07,660 --> 00:15:09,710
Please don't worry about me
and focus on your work.

196
00:15:10,860 --> 00:15:11,870
Sure. I'll see you.

197
00:15:32,550 --> 00:15:34,030
I'm home.

198
00:15:38,560 --> 00:15:41,180
Wait. Why are you eating
two portions alone?

199
00:15:41,530 --> 00:15:43,340
One must be for me.

200
00:15:43,490 --> 00:15:44,840
Not exactly.

201
00:15:44,900 --> 00:15:47,180
Then who is it for?

202
00:15:48,770 --> 00:15:50,390
I bought them both for me.

203
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:51,910
Boy, you're selfish.

204
00:15:52,670 --> 00:15:55,490
You joined a good soccer
club all by yourself...

205
00:15:55,570 --> 00:15:57,590
and now you're eating two
plates of the same sushi.

206
00:15:58,740 --> 00:16:01,200
- You've changed. You know that?
- That's not it.

207
00:16:02,880 --> 00:16:04,260
Starting now,

208
00:16:05,780 --> 00:16:07,770
I'll teach you the virtue of sharing.

209
00:16:09,890 --> 00:16:13,090
Watch and learn.
This is how a society works.

210
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:19,740
See?

211
00:16:20,530 --> 00:16:21,680
Eat up then.

212
00:16:23,970 --> 00:16:26,360
What do you mean you have something to say?

213
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:30,400
It's nothing big. The actors
signed with my agency...

214
00:16:30,410 --> 00:16:32,020
are getting more jobs overseas...

215
00:16:32,280 --> 00:16:34,230
which means a variety of global contracts.

216
00:16:34,410 --> 00:16:37,070
I was thinking about hiring a law firm...

217
00:16:37,150 --> 00:16:38,560
as our legal adviser.

218
00:16:41,890 --> 00:16:43,940
So you want our firm on retainer.

219
00:16:44,320 --> 00:16:46,750
I'm not sure. I get what you're saying,

220
00:16:46,760 --> 00:16:49,380
- but it might not be up to you.
- What?

221
00:16:49,730 --> 00:16:53,200
I'm sure you're aware of
the hottest case in Korea.

222
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:54,230
It's the Im Yun Hee Case.

223
00:16:54,230 --> 00:16:55,480
Who solved it?

224
00:16:56,130 --> 00:16:58,160
Always Law Firm did.

225
00:17:00,570 --> 00:17:02,970
If you're going to say something,
at least say the truth.

226
00:17:02,970 --> 00:17:05,010
It was Attorney Kwon's doing,
not your firm's.

227
00:17:05,010 --> 00:17:07,110
He may be a jerk, but he's talented.

228
00:17:07,110 --> 00:17:08,220
Anyway,

229
00:17:09,510 --> 00:17:12,650
because of it, my law
firm has been in demand.

230
00:17:12,750 --> 00:17:16,720
The same goes for me as well
since I'm its owner and leader.

231
00:17:16,890 --> 00:17:18,180
TV shows and magazines...

232
00:17:18,190 --> 00:17:22,230
are all dying to get an interview with me.

233
00:17:22,360 --> 00:17:24,140
I'm being contacted left and right.

234
00:17:24,360 --> 00:17:26,630
Does that mean you won't
take us on as a client?

235
00:17:26,630 --> 00:17:28,630
That's not what I'm saying.

236
00:17:28,630 --> 00:17:32,400
I'm just saying that we might
not always be available.

237
00:17:33,740 --> 00:17:36,130
That's too bad. Not available, you say?

238
00:17:36,840 --> 00:17:40,470
If you take us on as a client,
you'll enjoy a year-end party...

239
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:42,160
with the actors and artists.

240
00:17:43,850 --> 00:17:46,740
Also, in the summer at Waikiki Beach,

241
00:17:46,920 --> 00:17:48,560
we'll go camping and play beach volleyball.

242
00:17:49,150 --> 00:17:50,400
Toss!

243
00:17:50,890 --> 00:17:52,070
My ball!

244
00:17:52,460 --> 00:17:54,880
You could enjoy it too,
so I'm sad to hear that.

245
00:17:54,890 --> 00:17:55,970
You should get going then.

246
00:17:59,160 --> 00:18:02,830
Jun Seok, my little brother Jun Seok.

247
00:18:03,170 --> 00:18:05,790
Don't you know a joke when you hear one?

248
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:08,530
Did you think I'd ignore
my brother's request?

249
00:18:08,870 --> 00:18:12,210
How do you get by in life being this naive?

250
00:18:12,440 --> 00:18:14,170
Bring me the contract,
and I'll sign it instantly.

251
00:18:14,180 --> 00:18:16,100
My big brother!

252
00:18:16,710 --> 00:18:17,720
Gosh.

253
00:18:17,910 --> 00:18:21,680
Also, the team working on
Yun Seo's TV series...

254
00:18:21,950 --> 00:18:23,700
is looking for an advisory counsel.

255
00:18:23,790 --> 00:18:24,860
An advisory counsel?

256
00:18:24,860 --> 00:18:27,090
You know, an expert...

257
00:18:27,090 --> 00:18:30,490
who advises the staff and
writers on legal jargon.

258
00:18:30,530 --> 00:18:34,260
They're looking for someone
who Yun Seo knows well.

259
00:18:34,260 --> 00:18:36,250
I can be that expert. There's me.

260
00:18:37,970 --> 00:18:40,460
- You're an attorney too, right?
- Of course I am.

261
00:18:40,940 --> 00:18:41,950
It's too bad though.

262
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:45,250
You said you're not available.

263
00:18:45,540 --> 00:18:47,220
Can you ask someone else to do it?

264
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:50,280
My cute little brother, just let me do it.

265
00:18:50,280 --> 00:18:51,960
No, you make me nervous.

266
00:18:52,050 --> 00:18:55,010
You'll probably annoy the actors on set...

267
00:18:55,050 --> 00:18:57,510
and make animated photos.

268
00:18:57,620 --> 00:18:59,430
Have someone else do it.

269
00:18:59,860 --> 00:19:01,740
I doubt anyone would be willing to do it.

270
00:19:02,060 --> 00:19:03,300
An advisory counsel?

271
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:06,220
Yes, I'm sure no one would like to do it.

272
00:19:06,330 --> 00:19:08,870
It's exhausting, it's a hassle,
and it'll waste your time.

273
00:19:08,870 --> 00:19:09,990
I doubt anyone would want to do it.

274
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:11,550
No, I don't.

275
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:14,340
I have enough cases on my plate right now,

276
00:19:14,340 --> 00:19:17,060
and I don't want entertainment agencies...

277
00:19:17,310 --> 00:19:20,310
handing out there business
cards trying to scout me.

278
00:19:20,540 --> 00:19:21,660
I'll pass too.

279
00:19:21,950 --> 00:19:24,800
Okay, then I'll take the job.

280
00:19:25,350 --> 00:19:27,140
I bet you're delighted.

281
00:19:27,150 --> 00:19:29,640
You'll see Ms. Oh often when you're on set.

282
00:19:29,750 --> 00:19:32,010
Well, I guess that's highly possible.

283
00:19:32,660 --> 00:19:34,470
I heard they need an advisory
counsel starting today,

284
00:19:34,560 --> 00:19:36,850
so I'll be the one to do it.

285
00:19:37,190 --> 00:19:38,200
No.

286
00:19:40,230 --> 00:19:41,270
I'll do it.

287
00:19:46,870 --> 00:19:48,700
Am I hearing things right now?

288
00:19:48,710 --> 00:19:51,090
Mr. Kwon, can you say that one more time?

289
00:19:52,610 --> 00:19:55,300
I said, "I will do it."
The advisory counsel.

290
00:19:59,150 --> 00:20:01,810
Mr. Kwon, don't you hate
those kinds of things?

291
00:20:03,990 --> 00:20:05,030
Yes, well...

292
00:20:05,290 --> 00:20:07,640
It sounds like a good idea
to gain more experience.

293
00:20:10,790 --> 00:20:14,900
Mr. Kwon, if someone does something
that he usually never does, he dies.

294
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:18,160
So don't mind stuff like this as per usual,

295
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:20,190
and keep up the fight for justice.

296
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:22,460
No. I will be the advisory counsel.

297
00:20:22,510 --> 00:20:24,590
What's your problem? You're so annoying.

298
00:20:24,610 --> 00:20:27,230
Is it because of the interview
from the Park Su Myeong Case...

299
00:20:27,240 --> 00:20:29,610
a few days ago? Are you enjoying
all the attention or what?

300
00:20:29,610 --> 00:20:31,240
Why are you trying to show off?

301
00:20:31,250 --> 00:20:32,290
I'm not showing off.

302
00:20:32,580 --> 00:20:34,280
Why did you ask for volunteers
in the first place then?

303
00:20:34,280 --> 00:20:36,030
Forget it. Let's vote then.

304
00:20:36,090 --> 00:20:37,100
Vote?

305
00:20:37,520 --> 00:20:40,290
Yes. If he makes a mistake
at the filming site,

306
00:20:40,290 --> 00:20:42,030
he'll ruin the reputation of our law firm.

307
00:20:42,030 --> 00:20:45,260
So let's vote on who will
represent Always Law Firm.

308
00:20:45,860 --> 00:20:48,920
Let's see who is more
fit for this position.

309
00:20:48,930 --> 00:20:52,500
Just like democratic citizens,
let's decide by voting on it.

310
00:20:57,510 --> 00:21:00,570
(Yeon Joon Gyu, 1 vote
Kwon Jung Rok, 4 votes)

311
00:21:04,510 --> 00:21:05,990
I'll get going then.

312
00:21:23,930 --> 00:21:25,780
Ms. Oh Jin Sim. I have good news.

313
00:21:26,400 --> 00:21:28,110
We have a chance to finally meet.

314
00:21:28,740 --> 00:21:31,070
I will visit your filming site...

315
00:21:31,070 --> 00:21:32,720
as an advisory counsel...

316
00:21:36,850 --> 00:21:39,440
No, I'll surprise her.

317
00:21:45,460 --> 00:21:48,040
(Filming Team)

318
00:21:49,230 --> 00:21:51,510
Is it because I didn't see
Mr. Kwon last night?

319
00:21:51,830 --> 00:21:55,630
I have no energy, and no appetite either.

320
00:21:57,770 --> 00:21:58,780
I see.

321
00:21:59,370 --> 00:22:02,060
I see you've left two radishes
because you have no appetite.

322
00:22:02,840 --> 00:22:04,930
It's so squeaky clean people might
think you licked everything off.

323
00:22:06,040 --> 00:22:08,160
I said I don't have an appetite.
I didn't say I don't like rice.

324
00:22:09,910 --> 00:22:13,450
Yun Seo, I'm happy that you eat so well.

325
00:22:13,550 --> 00:22:16,170
I'm very happy, but you
have to watch your figure.

326
00:22:16,550 --> 00:22:19,550
What if your face is all swollen up on TV?

327
00:22:19,610 --> 00:22:22,060
By the way, you know you have
a photo shoot next week, right?

328
00:22:22,210 --> 00:22:26,180
Yes, I know. Don't worry.
I have a conscience too, you know.

329
00:22:29,050 --> 00:22:31,550
I heard this is helpful,
so I'm drinking it constantly.

330
00:22:31,550 --> 00:22:35,800
Good. Gosh, you look like you're
shooting a commercial right now.

331
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:37,500
Drink some more.

332
00:22:38,360 --> 00:22:40,850
- Mr. Gong, can we talk?
- Sure.

333
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:50,490
I miss Mr. Kwon.

334
00:22:52,010 --> 00:22:55,100
I never expected Mr. Kwon
doing something like that.

335
00:22:55,110 --> 00:22:56,400
Tell me about it.

336
00:22:56,410 --> 00:22:59,680
It's unbelievable,
like seeing a mirage in a desert.

337
00:23:02,180 --> 00:23:05,140
Hey, you're all gathered here.
Is it tea time?

338
00:23:06,250 --> 00:23:07,760
Oh, boy. That looks tasty.

339
00:23:09,460 --> 00:23:12,380
Oh, right. From now on,
during our meetings,

340
00:23:12,490 --> 00:23:14,270
I wish someone will take
some meeting minutes.

341
00:23:14,690 --> 00:23:16,880
The typing sound from
the laptop is too loud,

342
00:23:16,930 --> 00:23:19,750
so I think someone should
handwrite some meeting minutes.

343
00:23:20,270 --> 00:23:21,740
Okay. I'll do it.

344
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:23,740
Oh, Hae Yeong?
Do you have good handwriting?

345
00:23:23,740 --> 00:23:24,740
Yes.

346
00:23:24,740 --> 00:23:28,510
But I think it should be someone
who has some neat handwriting.

347
00:23:29,380 --> 00:23:32,600
To find out, why don't we all
write down some letters?

348
00:23:32,610 --> 00:23:35,250
Write, "Minutes of Meeting" on this.

349
00:23:35,250 --> 00:23:36,430
"Minutes of Meeting".

350
00:23:37,220 --> 00:23:39,440
We should make sure, just in case.

351
00:23:42,890 --> 00:23:45,180
(Minutes of Meeting)

352
00:23:48,960 --> 00:23:50,740
(Minutes of Meeting)

353
00:23:56,140 --> 00:23:58,160
I found it. It's this.

354
00:23:58,270 --> 00:24:00,490
This letter looks the same.

355
00:24:03,610 --> 00:24:05,360
Mr. Choi, Ms. Dan, Hae Yeong, and Ms. Yang.

356
00:24:06,010 --> 00:24:08,000
I'm very disappointed in you.
I never expected this.

357
00:24:08,950 --> 00:24:12,250
I was always so nice to you,
yet you betrayed me and chose Mr. Kwon?

358
00:24:13,490 --> 00:24:15,100
What are you talking about?

359
00:24:15,390 --> 00:24:17,060
I chose you.

360
00:24:17,060 --> 00:24:20,080
You received one vote, right? That was me.

361
00:24:20,090 --> 00:24:21,100
Liar.

362
00:24:21,660 --> 00:24:22,940
Look at this.

363
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:25,800
I compared your handwritings when
you wrote Kwon Jung Rok's name...

364
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:28,290
to the handwritings that
you wrote just now.

365
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:30,690
This handwriting is the
only one that I don't have.

366
00:24:30,700 --> 00:24:32,420
This is the only one.

367
00:24:32,770 --> 00:24:35,030
Ms. Yang, it seems like you
thought a lot about this.

368
00:24:36,040 --> 00:24:39,050
You said it was an anonymous vote.
How could you do this?

369
00:24:39,050 --> 00:24:41,280
I didn't say anything.
I was simply curious.

370
00:24:41,280 --> 00:24:43,500
Don't worry, I won't discriminate
anyone over something like this.

371
00:24:43,850 --> 00:24:46,920
But why is there so much
dust suddenly in this place?

372
00:24:47,050 --> 00:24:49,140
We should all gather this weekend...

373
00:24:49,220 --> 00:24:51,320
and clean this place up thoroughly.

374
00:24:51,320 --> 00:24:52,740
Except for you, Mr. Lee.

375
00:24:53,330 --> 00:24:55,480
I'll give you a movie ticket,
so go watch a movie.

376
00:25:04,870 --> 00:25:07,130
- Hello.
- Hello.

377
00:25:07,140 --> 00:25:08,130
Hello.

378
00:25:08,140 --> 00:25:10,230
The advisory counsel for
our drama has arrived.

379
00:25:24,020 --> 00:25:26,650
Mr. Kwon, can you go over
this script with me?

380
00:25:29,360 --> 00:25:30,510
(Waiting Room, Oh Yun Seo)

381
00:25:31,560 --> 00:25:33,490
Why on earth are you here?

382
00:25:33,730 --> 00:25:35,160
How did you come?

383
00:25:35,170 --> 00:25:37,110
You're the advisory counsel for our drama?

384
00:25:37,940 --> 00:25:41,200
It wasn't easy to be elected
as an advisory counsel.

385
00:25:41,210 --> 00:25:42,650
- Elected?
- Yes.

386
00:25:42,810 --> 00:25:45,810
Mr. Yeon, who enjoys being exposed
to the public, outright revealed...

387
00:25:45,950 --> 00:25:49,550
his ambition that he wanted
to be your advisory counsel.

388
00:25:49,650 --> 00:25:52,270
However, out of my
determination to see you,

389
00:25:52,320 --> 00:25:54,540
and despite Mr. Yeon's
persuasion and criticism,

390
00:25:54,590 --> 00:25:56,740
we eventually decided to
vote on it democratically.

391
00:25:56,990 --> 00:26:00,530
And I won by an overwhelming
score of 4 to 1. I have been...

392
00:26:00,530 --> 00:26:03,990
proudly elected as the advisory
counsel of your drama!

393
00:26:06,730 --> 00:26:09,770
If I think about it now, it was a
really thrilling and close fight.

394
00:26:11,400 --> 00:26:14,440
It does indeed sound thrilling.

395
00:26:14,470 --> 00:26:17,870
Yes. Once I came here and saw your face,

396
00:26:17,980 --> 00:26:20,200
I realized it was a great choice
to participate in the vote.

397
00:26:21,810 --> 00:26:24,300
But do you feel uncomfortable
or pressured...

398
00:26:24,580 --> 00:26:27,310
- because of my sudden visit?
- No way.

399
00:26:27,450 --> 00:26:29,940
Do you know how happy I feel right now?

400
00:26:30,290 --> 00:26:32,910
I missed you so much too.

401
00:26:35,360 --> 00:26:36,710
Yun Seo, are you in here?

402
00:26:40,100 --> 00:26:41,640
I'm sorry. No.

403
00:26:42,300 --> 00:26:43,410
How have you been? No.

404
00:26:43,570 --> 00:26:45,930
- Yun Seo. Oh Yun Seo!
- What?

405
00:26:46,470 --> 00:26:48,280
We're starting the shoot.
You have to come out now.

406
00:26:48,540 --> 00:26:50,540
Okay, I'm on my way.

407
00:26:50,540 --> 00:26:53,000
- Mr. Kwon, you should come too.
- Okay.

408
00:26:56,020 --> 00:26:57,060
What's wrong?

409
00:26:59,650 --> 00:27:02,850
Mr. Kwon, I understand how you feel,

410
00:27:02,990 --> 00:27:05,790
but coming here as an advisory
counsel seems a bit...

411
00:27:05,790 --> 00:27:07,170
That's my free will.

412
00:27:07,230 --> 00:27:09,550
Interfering with our relationship
all the time like this...

413
00:27:09,630 --> 00:27:11,420
is an invasion of one's freedom
to pursue happiness...

414
00:27:11,430 --> 00:27:13,550
and freedom of action, which is
guaranteed by the constitution.

415
00:27:13,670 --> 00:27:15,760
- Then...
- Okay.

416
00:27:18,440 --> 00:27:20,960
Yun Seo, don't go.
Don't go with him. Wait for me.

417
00:27:22,680 --> 00:27:26,340
Witness, you said you were at home
at the day of the incident.

418
00:27:27,310 --> 00:27:28,420
Is that correct?

419
00:27:31,150 --> 00:27:32,460
Your Honor.

420
00:27:35,120 --> 00:27:37,410
Wait, I have a question.

421
00:27:38,490 --> 00:27:39,500
Mr. Kwon?

422
00:27:40,190 --> 00:27:42,820
When I say, "Your Honor",

423
00:27:43,530 --> 00:27:45,820
what is the proper hand gesture?

424
00:27:46,100 --> 00:27:47,110
Oh, that.

425
00:27:47,830 --> 00:27:49,760
Okay. Thanks.

426
00:27:53,540 --> 00:27:56,330
Instead of pointing at the judge directly,

427
00:27:57,040 --> 00:28:00,780
you should stand straight or
gather your hands together.

428
00:28:00,780 --> 00:28:02,130
This looks good.

429
00:28:03,480 --> 00:28:04,560
Instead of this?

430
00:28:04,980 --> 00:28:06,700
Using both hands is too weird.

431
00:28:06,990 --> 00:28:08,130
You should stand straight...

432
00:28:10,710 --> 00:28:14,880
♫ <i>Hey you quiet and serious person,
you keep looking at me, right?</i> ♫

433
00:28:15,290 --> 00:28:16,640
Your Honor.

434
00:28:17,012 --> 00:28:20,060
♫ <i>Yes, slowly and calmly</i> ♫

435
00:28:20,170 --> 00:28:22,360
Mr. Kwon, have some coffee.

436
00:28:22,640 --> 00:28:23,680
Thank you.

437
00:28:23,819 --> 00:28:27,060
♫ <i>Whenever, wherever, be flexible,
that's my specialty</i> ♫

438
00:28:27,740 --> 00:28:30,030
Excuse me, Mr. Kwon Jung Rok?

439
00:28:31,780 --> 00:28:34,810
This part in the script is bothering me.
Is this...

440
00:28:34,910 --> 00:28:36,730
legally a correct expression?

441
00:28:38,420 --> 00:28:39,760
(Kwon Jung Rok)

442
00:28:40,460 --> 00:28:44,200
♫ <i>It's too hard, tell me with easier words</i> ♫

443
00:28:44,260 --> 00:28:47,320
Yes. It's a very precise
expression with no errors at all.

444
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:49,730
♫ <i>Can you see my heart over there?</i> ♫

445
00:28:49,730 --> 00:28:50,770
Yes.

446
00:28:51,200 --> 00:28:52,580
Of course there aren't.

447
00:28:52,700 --> 00:28:55,320
I can see this script has no errors at all.

448
00:28:55,440 --> 00:28:57,010
So can we please move on to the next scene?

449
00:28:57,440 --> 00:28:58,480
Come here. Follow me.

450
00:28:59,200 --> 00:29:01,510
♫ <i>You're gonna fall for me</i> ♫

451
00:29:01,510 --> 00:29:04,400
♫ <i>Hurry and show yourself</i> ♫

452
00:29:04,460 --> 00:29:07,560
♫ <i>Yeah, what you gonna do,
what you gonna do, woo hoo!</i> ♫

453
00:29:26,000 --> 00:29:27,040
Ms. Dan.

454
00:29:28,940 --> 00:29:31,790
Although our contract dating is over,
we're still colleagues.

455
00:29:32,100 --> 00:29:34,290
Why don't you ever talk to me
and keep ignoring me?

456
00:29:34,340 --> 00:29:35,380
Did I?

457
00:29:35,580 --> 00:29:38,000
If I did, I'm sorry.

458
00:29:38,980 --> 00:29:39,990
Wait.

459
00:29:41,210 --> 00:29:44,000
Are things going well with the
delivery guy you fell for...

460
00:29:44,920 --> 00:29:46,430
- and chased after?
- No.

461
00:29:46,920 --> 00:29:49,150
I only did that out of habit
because I was drunk.

462
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:50,530
But it was nothing sincere.

463
00:29:50,760 --> 00:29:53,850
Anyway, I wasn't supposed
to flirt with anyone else,

464
00:29:53,860 --> 00:29:55,960
but I failed to stick to it
until our contract ended...

465
00:29:55,960 --> 00:29:57,340
and broke the contract by doing so.

466
00:29:58,160 --> 00:30:00,150
I'm sorry about that.

467
00:30:00,330 --> 00:30:01,610
You should be sorry.

468
00:30:02,640 --> 00:30:03,680
I'm not quite sure about that.

469
00:30:03,740 --> 00:30:06,770
It's not like you did
everything right either.

470
00:30:07,210 --> 00:30:10,060
You told me that your heart
feels numb when you're with me.

471
00:30:10,210 --> 00:30:13,280
There was no point in continuing
our dating contract...

472
00:30:13,510 --> 00:30:14,520
with someone who had no feelings for me.

473
00:30:15,210 --> 00:30:18,210
I was practically making
a fool out of myself.

474
00:30:18,420 --> 00:30:21,240
Well, then. I'll be off now.

475
00:30:28,690 --> 00:30:31,380
What was that? She used to look at me...

476
00:30:31,560 --> 00:30:33,570
with hearts in her eyes.

477
00:30:33,570 --> 00:30:35,520
But now, she's so cold toward me.

478
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:37,890
How can someone change so drastically?

479
00:30:39,270 --> 00:30:41,260
Gosh, my heart. It hurts.

480
00:30:48,380 --> 00:30:49,490
Was I too mean?

481
00:30:52,520 --> 00:30:55,370
No, there's no point in
apologizing to a guy...

482
00:30:55,990 --> 00:30:57,170
who has no feelings for me.

483
00:30:59,590 --> 00:31:00,740
Let's get over him.

484
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:06,080
For some reason,

485
00:31:09,640 --> 00:31:11,280
it feels as if my heart is empty.

486
00:31:11,500 --> 00:31:12,820
Why do I feel this way?

487
00:31:24,080 --> 00:31:25,550
(Short-term Dating Contract)

488
00:31:25,550 --> 00:31:28,310
Whatever the case,
our contract has come to end.

489
00:31:29,760 --> 00:31:31,170
So let's forget about her now.

490
00:31:34,230 --> 00:31:35,240
Goodbye.

491
00:31:37,130 --> 00:31:38,310
It's time to say goodbye...

492
00:31:39,700 --> 00:31:40,840
to this chapter in my life...

493
00:31:41,630 --> 00:31:43,350
that was full of clumsiness and innocence.

494
00:31:54,980 --> 00:31:57,320
Gosh, that's hot! That's so hot!

495
00:31:57,320 --> 00:31:59,100
Goodness, that's so hot!

496
00:32:34,050 --> 00:32:35,160
Do you need anything?

497
00:32:38,520 --> 00:32:39,570
No, I'm just here for no reason.

498
00:32:43,130 --> 00:32:45,320
Working as an advisory counsel
must've worn you out...

499
00:32:45,700 --> 00:32:48,090
seeing that you're starting
the day with a cup of coffee.

500
00:32:49,400 --> 00:32:52,040
I can imagine why. You're already
in charge of so many cases.

501
00:32:52,040 --> 00:32:53,950
But you're even working as
an advisory counsel now.

502
00:32:54,070 --> 00:32:55,520
So it's only natural that you're tired.

503
00:32:57,040 --> 00:33:00,080
It seems like you really
regret having taken the job.

504
00:33:01,250 --> 00:33:04,680
Okay, I'll sacrifice myself on your behalf.

505
00:33:04,720 --> 00:33:07,080
Although it may be bothersome and tiring,

506
00:33:07,090 --> 00:33:09,540
I'll take your place and
become Yun Seo's advisory counsel.

507
00:33:09,720 --> 00:33:10,720
That's okay.

508
00:33:10,720 --> 00:33:12,570
Really? I see.

509
00:33:13,560 --> 00:33:14,640
I guess it's not that bad.

510
00:33:15,230 --> 00:33:16,310
By the way,

