787
00:50:42,920 --> 00:50:43,970
Okay.

788
00:50:53,770 --> 00:50:54,780
Jung Do.

789
00:50:57,520 --> 00:50:58,760
How did you come here?

790
00:50:58,920 --> 00:51:00,800
Shouldn't you be in Israel?
Why are you here?

791
00:51:01,210 --> 00:51:02,600
I came in order to leave no regrets.

792
00:51:02,880 --> 00:51:05,640
In order not to regret letting
you go for the rest of my life.

793
00:51:23,170 --> 00:51:24,790
Cut. What was that?

794
00:51:25,480 --> 00:51:26,990
Was that a car horn?

795
00:51:27,900 --> 00:51:29,390
Make sure there aren't
any unnecessary sounds.

796
00:51:30,520 --> 00:51:32,460
All right, stand by. Let's try it again.

797
00:51:32,580 --> 00:51:35,140
Hold on... Wait a minute.

798
00:51:38,150 --> 00:51:40,610
May I say something
as the advisory counsel?

799
00:51:40,790 --> 00:51:42,100
Yes, of course.

800
00:51:42,330 --> 00:51:45,520
I know it's a drama,
but a man and woman kissing...

801
00:51:45,520 --> 00:51:48,250
in front of the court like
this seems so unrealistic.

802
00:51:48,770 --> 00:51:51,560
On top of that, how could an
attorney and a judicial officer...

803
00:51:51,670 --> 00:51:53,550
kiss in front of a sacred court?

804
00:51:53,900 --> 00:51:56,690
From my perspective, as a man
who works in this industry,

805
00:51:56,730 --> 00:51:59,830
I'm afraid this scene
is a bit inappropriate.

806
00:51:59,840 --> 00:52:01,620
This is a very conservative place.

807
00:52:04,540 --> 00:52:07,880
Still, if there needs to be some
sort of emotional exchange,

808
00:52:09,690 --> 00:52:11,600
I believe a hug will be appropriate.

809
00:52:11,750 --> 00:52:13,880
- A hug?
- No, forget that.

810
00:52:13,880 --> 00:52:15,840
Not even a hug.

811
00:52:17,150 --> 00:52:18,160
A handshake.

812
00:52:18,590 --> 00:52:20,560
A handshake sounds perfect.

813
00:52:20,560 --> 00:52:22,890
Mr. Kwon, let's go get some coffee.

814
00:52:23,630 --> 00:52:24,660
I don't want coffee.

815
00:52:24,670 --> 00:52:26,650
No, you and I should get some coffee.

816
00:52:28,540 --> 00:52:31,710
You told me not to interfere,
mentioning something about...

817
00:52:31,770 --> 00:52:34,630
one's right to pursue happiness.

818
00:52:35,000 --> 00:52:37,240
What do you think you're doing right now?

819
00:52:38,210 --> 00:52:41,140
I just did my job as an advisory counsel.

820
00:52:41,150 --> 00:52:43,980
If you came as an advisory counsel,
you should give advice.

821
00:52:43,980 --> 00:52:46,000
Why are you being jealous?

822
00:52:46,380 --> 00:52:49,210
- It's not jealousy.
- It is jealousy.

823
00:52:50,690 --> 00:52:53,180
Look at that. Mr. Kwon, look over there.

824
00:52:53,420 --> 00:52:56,320
You said judicial officers are
conservative or something.

825
00:52:56,400 --> 00:52:59,530
But look at how they're holding hands.
Conservative my foot.

826
00:52:59,540 --> 00:53:02,530
Oh, well... That's ridiculous.

827
00:53:02,540 --> 00:53:05,570
This industry is very conservative.
There's no way...

828
00:53:09,110 --> 00:53:10,120
Kim Se Won?

829
00:53:12,520 --> 00:53:13,530
Jung Rok.

830
00:53:14,020 --> 00:53:15,260
Jung Rok?

831
00:53:15,980 --> 00:53:17,730
You even know them?

832
00:53:19,610 --> 00:53:20,720
I don't.

833
00:53:20,730 --> 00:53:22,910
Kim Se Won. Jung Rok.

834
00:53:23,230 --> 00:53:24,550
I have my right to take the Fifth.

835
00:53:24,560 --> 00:53:26,070
Goodness, you're just full of jealousy.

836
00:53:30,500 --> 00:53:34,000
Can you hold hands like that
in court in those robes?

837
00:53:34,540 --> 00:53:37,570
Who cares? It's not like we're
not working because we're dating.

838
00:53:37,580 --> 00:53:40,230
I just got tired of dating
secretly all the time.

839
00:53:40,980 --> 00:53:44,780
I just decided to open about it
without worrying about others.

840
00:53:45,340 --> 00:53:48,750
Me too. I usually would never
have imagined doing this,

841
00:53:49,250 --> 00:53:50,870
but Se Won was right.

842
00:53:51,310 --> 00:53:54,250
It was hard at first, but once I
got used to it, it's nothing.

843
00:53:55,980 --> 00:53:58,320
Jung Rok, what should I do?

844
00:53:58,690 --> 00:54:00,610
I think I'm taking after Se Won.

845
00:54:03,360 --> 00:54:04,710
Fine, whatever.

846
00:54:31,960 --> 00:54:36,300
- Cheers to Always Law Firm!
- Cheers!

847
00:54:42,400 --> 00:54:45,170
So, how did you two start to
get attracted to each other?

848
00:54:45,170 --> 00:54:48,170
I know. You used to be enemies before.

849
00:54:49,080 --> 00:54:51,210
I'm not saying this
because he's my boyfriend.

850
00:54:51,210 --> 00:54:53,910
But Mr. Choi was a man born to be loved.

851
